Competition Doom is a Doom source port based on Chocolate Doom and
adds additional features and settings to it.


== Configuration File ==

Competition Doom also provides some extra settings.
These are stored in a file named 'cndoom.cfg'.

Detailed explanation about each setting:

// Display ingame/intermission screen timer
// 0 - No. 1 - Yes (Default)
 cn_timer_enabled              1

// Timer X position
// Default: -1
 cn_timer_offset_x             -1

// Timer Y position
// Default: 0
 cn_timer_offset_y             0

// Timer color
// 0 - 255 (Default:168)
 cn_timer_color_index          168

// Shadow for timer
// 0 - No (Default). 1 - Yes
 cn_timer_shadow_index         0

// Backgroung color for timer
// 0 - 255 (Default:16)
 cn_timer_bg_colormap          16

// Quickstart delay so monitor can change resolution and
// let you adjust mouse and keys before the game starts.
// 0 - 99999 (Default:1500)
 cn_quickstart_delay           1500

// Your details (All required for demo submission)
 cn_meta_firstname
 cn_meta_lastname
 cn_meta_nickname

// Country format: two letter ISO 3166, example for USA (us)
// http://goo.gl/Bn8d3
 cn_meta_country

// Extra details not required (Optional)
// Date format: YYYY-MM-DD
 cn_meta_birthdate
 cn_meta_email
 cn_meta_url 


== Additional command-line options ==

 -printstats        Outputs demo stats (time, kills, items) to
                    stdout.txt, use this when playing demo:
                    eg. "cndoom -playdemo demo.lmp -printstats"
                    Should be useful for movie and episode runs.


